  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "Rockruff is a versatile Pok\u00e9mon that can be built for both physical and special attacking roles, but its physical Attack stat is generally more favorable. Here\u2019s a solid moveset for Rockruff in **Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon** that focuses on its physical capabilities:\n\n### **Rockruff Moveset (Physical Attacker)**\n- **Stone Edge**  \n  - Type: Rock  \n  - Power: 100 | Accuracy: 80  \n  - Rockruff's signature STAB (Same-Type Attack Bonus) move. It\u2019s a powerful Rock-type move that deals heavy damage, though it has lower accuracy.\n\n- **Crunch**  \n  - Type: Dark  \n  - Power: 80 | Accuracy: 100  \n  - A reliable Dark-type move that provides good coverage against Psychic and Ghost types. It also has a chance to lower the target\u2019s Defense.\n\n- **Earthquake**  \n  - Type: Ground  \n  - Power: 100 | Accuracy: 100  \n  - A strong Ground-type move that covers Rockruff\u2019s weaknesses to Steel and Electric types. It\u2019s a great option for coverage.\n\n- **Iron Head**  \n  - Type: Steel  \n  - Power: 80 | Accuracy: 100  \n  - A Steel-type move that can deal with Fairy, Ice, and Rock types. It also has a chance to make the target flinch.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Options**\n- **Swords Dance** (if you want Rockruff to set up and sweep)  \n  - Boosts Rockruff's Attack by two stages, making it even more dangerous.\n\n- **Rock Tomb**  \n  - A weaker Rock-type move with 95% accuracy, but lowers the target\u2019s Speed. Useful for utility.\n\n- **Fire Fang**  \n  - Covers Grass and Steel types, but is generally less reliable than the other moves.\n\n---\n\n### **Nature and EVs**\n- **Nature:** Adamant (+Attack, -Special Attack) or Jolly (+Speed, -Special Attack)  \n  - Adamant maximizes Rockruff\u2019s physical damage, while Jolly boosts its Speed to outspeed opponents.\n\n- **EVs:**  \n  - 252 Attack / 252 Speed / 4 HP  \n  - This EV spread ensures Rockruff hits hard and fast.\n\n---\n\n### **Ability**\n- **Keen Eye** (prevents accuracy drops)  \n- **Steadfast** (boosts Speed if flinched)  \n- **Vital Spirit** (prevents sleep)  \n  - All of Rockruff\u2019s abilities are decent, but none are game-changing. Choose based on preference or team needs.\n\n---\n\nThis moveset makes Rockruff a strong physical attacker with good coverage and utility. If you\u2019re using it in the story or casual play, this setup should work great!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
